    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When using your Destroy alter ability, you may target the moving components of a lock in lieu of targeting the whole lock, allowing you to disable it without destroying the entire device. When attempting to disable a complex device or lock you may attempt Disable Device checks as if it was a class skill using your caster level in place of skill ranks and your casting ability modifier in place of Dexterity. Doing so requires a standard action, regardless of how long a typical Disable Device check would take. If you possess Potent Alteration you may spend a spell point to disarm magical traps.</p>\n",
